---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../data/tools';

const lastUpdated = 'May 23, 2026';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Workspace Lux"
  description="Privacy policy for Workspace Lux covering analytics, cookies, advertising, and contact form data."
  path="/privacy-policy"
>
  <article class="max-w-site mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-10 prose-content">
    <header class="mb-10">
      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-main mb-4">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-muted">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    </header>

    <p>
      Workspace Lux (“we”, “us”, “our”) operates {SITE.url}. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect,
      use, and protect information when you visit our website or contact us.
    </p>

    <h2>Information we collect</h2>
    <h3>Usage and analytics</h3>
    <p>
      We may use privacy-friendly analytics services such as Cloudflare Web Analytics and/or Google
      Analytics to understand traffic patterns, popular pages, and general device or browser types.
      These services help us improve content and performance. Analytics data is typically aggregated and
      does not intentionally identify you personally.
    </p>
    <h3>Cookies and similar technologies</h3>
    <p>
      Our site may set essential cookies required for basic functionality. If we display advertising
      through Google AdSense or similar partners, those services may use cookies or similar identifiers
      to serve and measure ads, including personalized advertising where applicable and permitted by law.
      You can manage cookie preferences through your browser settings and, where offered, vendor opt-out
      tools.
    </p>
    <h3>Contact form and email</h3>
    <p>
      If you submit our contact form or email us directly, we receive the information you provide (such
      as name, email address, and message content). We use this information only to respond to your
      inquiry and maintain a record of correspondence as needed.
    </p>

    <h2>How we use information</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Operate, maintain, and improve the website and calculators</li>
      <li>Respond to messages and support requests</li>
      <li>Monitor security, abuse, and technical performance</li>
      <li>Comply with legal obligations</li>
      <li>Display advertising where enabled, subject to partner policies</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Third-party services</h2>
    <p>
      We may rely on third parties for hosting (e.g., Cloudflare Pages), analytics, advertising (e.g.,
      Google AdSense), and contact forms (e.g., Formspree). These providers process data under their
      own privacy policies. We encourage you to review those policies when you interact with embedded
      services or follow external links.
    </p>

    <h2>Data retention</h2>
    <p>
      Analytics data is retained according to each provider’s settings. Contact messages are kept only as
      long as needed to handle your request and for reasonable business records, unless a longer period
      is required by law.
    </p>

    <h2>Your rights</h2>
    <p>
      Depending on your location, you may have rights to access, correct, delete, or restrict processing
      of personal data, or to object to certain processing including targeted advertising. To exercise
      these rights, contact us at
      <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`} class="text-primary hover:underline">{SITE.email}</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Children</h2>
    <p>
      Our site is not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information
      from children.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The “Last updated” date at the top will change
      when we do. Continued use of the site after changes constitutes acceptance of the revised policy.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about this Privacy Policy? Email
      <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`} class="text-primary hover:underline">{SITE.email}</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
